From 198d2afcc488e0aff942480e7d0165258e905dfa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rohitraj45592 <rohitraj45592@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 08:27:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add Mock Interview page as an AI interview coach module

New route at /dashboard-v2/mock-interview, built with the existing
DashboardLayout, Header and the same monochrome design language used
across Overview, Career Twin, Resume Studio and Job Hub - no layout,
header, colors, radius, shadows or motion conventions changed.

16 sections per spec: hero with a monochrome interview-setup
illustration and floating badges, interview snapshot stats, 6
interview category cards, an interactive AI interview session card
(mic/camera toggle, progress, skip/end controls - UI only, no real
media APIs), a question panel with hints/topics/difficulty, two-column
AI feedback, an 8-metric performance breakdown with animated shine-
sweep bars, AI suggestions, interview history with retry, recent
activity, an FAQ accordion, coding practice difficulty cards, AI
communication tips, a placement readiness breakdown, achievement
badges, and export actions.

Reused the shared AnimatedNumber component and the pulse-ring /
shine-sweep keyframes already added for Career Twin instead of
duplicating that logic again.

Sidebar was updated directly in this same commit (Mock Interview item
now links to its route) per the task's explicit instruction not to
generate a separate sidebar patch.

UI only - no backend, API, auth, voice/camera APIs, or database -
realistic dummy data throughout.
